## Building a Chunked Drag-and-drop File Uploader in Angular

**Mental model:** A drop zone takes files via drag-drop or input. Each file splits into `ceil(size / chunkSize)` chunks uploaded sequentially, advancing a per-file progress bar; chunk size is configurable. Uploads are simulated. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them).

### Step 1 — Drop zone
```html
<div (dragover)="$event.preventDefault()" (drop)="onDrop($event)">
  <input type="file" multiple (change)="add($any($event.target).files)" />
</div>
```

### Step 2 — Model files
```typescript
add(list: FileList): void {
  const size = this.chunkKB * 1024;
  Array.from(list).forEach((f) => {
    const item = { id: this.uid(), name: f.name, size: f.size, sent: 0, total: Math.max(1, Math.ceil(f.size / size)) };
    this.files.push(item);
    this.upload(item);
  });
}
```

### Step 3 — Upload chunks
```typescript
upload(item: UploadFile): void {
  const id = setInterval(() => {
    if (item.sent >= item.total) { clearInterval(id); return; }
    item.sent++;
  }, 200);
  this.timers[item.id] = id;
}
```

### Step 4 — Progress
```html
<div [style.width.%]="(f.sent / f.total) * 100"></div>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Zero-byte file | `Math.max(1, …)`. |
| Missing preventDefault | Required on `(dragover)`. |
| Cleanup | Clear timers in `ngOnDestroy`. |

**Interview tip:** The `ceil(size/chunkSize)` chunk loop is the heart of "configurable chunk size" — the basis for resume/retry — and `[style.width.%]` is the clean progress-bar binding.

